news.title: Bombay HC dismisses MIDC petition against Embassy Developments on Nashik SEZ land
news.para: The Bombay High Court dismissed MIDC's eviction petition against Indiabulls Industrial Infrastructure for a Sinnar SEZ project, upholding interim relief. The dispute, stemming from a 2007 pact, involves MIDC's claims of undeveloped areas versus Indiabulls' defense of project complexities and sub-leasing. Embassy Developments now aims for an amicable resolution.

news.title: Seven new town planning schemes to be created by Ahmedabad development body
news.para: The Ahmedabad Urban Development Authority approved seven new Town Planning Schemes in villages like Saij and Godhavi during a recent board meeting. This decision aims to systematically develop approximately 1,000 hectares in satellite areas, providing land for infrastructure and new roads as Ahmedabad prepares to host major sporting events.

news.title: Tenant registrations to be cleared from any sub-registrar office in a given district now
news.para: Maharashtra's property registration department is implementing "One District, One Registration" from Oct 2, allowing any sub-registrar office to process tenant agreements, aiming to reduce delays and streamline services. Concurrently, e-Pramaan launched in Satara on Sept 17, enabling citizens to access digitally signed property documents online, enhancing convenience and transparency across the state.

news.title: Gujarat HC fines flat owners for stalling redevelopment
news.para: Gujarat High Court imposed a one lakh rupee fine. This penalty targeted dissenting members of Surya Apartments-2. They attempted to stall redevelopment through legal action. The court found their urgent hearing request created an emergency. This consumed court time. The court dismissed their appeal, citing frivolous litigation.

news.title: DTCP to launch sealing drive in Gurugram's Sushant Lok 2 & 3 to curb illegal construction
news.para: Gurugram's DTCP is launching a major sealing drive this week in Sushant Lok-2 and 3 against over 60 houses for unauthorised commercial activities and structural violations. This action follows ignored restoration orders and aims to curb widespread commercial misuse, addressing resident complaints about congestion and ensuring planned development in licensed colonies.

news.title: Sebi, stock exchanges waive fines, penalties on Unitech
news.para: Sebi, NSE, and BSE have waived fines on Unitech for past non-compliances and will shift its shares from the restricted Z category to actively traded B category from October 7.

news.title: Infopark, Cochin development body plan to set up integrated AI town by 2030
news.para: Kochi's proposed Infopark Phase III, an Integrated AI Township, is slated for completion by 2030 with a Rs 25,000 crore investment. This joint GCDA-Infopark project in Kizhakkambalam will generate 2 lakh direct jobs and feature advanced AI-controlled sustainable infrastructure. It aims to transform Kerala into a knowledge economy.

news.title: Lucknow civic body seals Sahara Group's land in Gomtinagar
news.para: Lucknow Municipal Corporation has sealed 170 acres of Sahara Group's land in Gomtinagar, including Subrato Kothi, due to license and lease violations. An inquiry found misuse of government land, leading to the cancellation of agreements. Meanwhile, Sahara seeks Supreme Court permission to sell Sahara City to Adani Properties to clear debts, a move LMC plans to challenge.

news.title: YEIDA cracks down on illegal sale of plots around Noida international airport
news.para: YEIDA has initiated a major crackdown on illegal colonizers promoting fraudulent "airport townships" near Noida International Airport. These scammers lure Delhi-NCR buyers with fake promises and illegal plots on government or agricultural land. The authority is taking strict action, including demolitions, FIRs, and considering a special investigation team to curb this widespread scam.

news.title: Maharashtra government sets up authority to expedite self-redevelopment projects
news.para: Maharashtra government appointed BJP MLC Pravin Darekar to head the new Self-Group Redevelopment Authority (SGRA), aiming to expedite self-redevelopment projects. Darekar, with Minister of State status, will oversee the authority, which encourages housing societies to undertake redevelopment themselves, retaining all benefits. This initiative follows recommendations to resolve past difficulties and boost self-redevelopment adoption.

news.title: FTC accuses Zillow of paying Redfin $100 million to stop competing on rental listings
news.para: The FTC has sued Zillow and Redfin, alleging Zillow paid Redfin $100 million to exit the online apartment rental listings market. This deal, which saw Redfin transfer its business and agree to a nine-year non-compete, is accused of suppressing competition, potentially increasing advertising costs, and reducing innovation for renters. Zillow maintains the partnership benefits consumers.

news.title: Net leasing of office spaces up 35% in Jul-Sep across top eight cities: C&W
news.para: India's office space net leasing surged 35 per cent to 16.25 million sq ft during July-September, driven by robust demand from domestic and overseas companies. While Delhi-NCR, Chennai, and Pune recorded significant growth, Mumbai and Bengaluru experienced declines. This indicates a widespread and sustained expansionary cycle in the sector.

news.title: Registration of properties in Mumbai up 32% in September 2025
news.para: Mumbai's property registrations surged by 32 per cent in September, reaching 12,070 units, driven by robust festive demand. This significant increase, reported by Knight Frank India, also saw stamp duty collections jump 47 per cent to Rs 1,292 crore. Residential properties constituted 80 per cent of these registrations, indicating strong housing market activity.

news.title: IPO-bound WeWork India posts ₹14.14 crore loss in April-June 2025
news.para: Co-working major WeWork India is launching its Rs 3,000 crore Initial Public Offering this week, with shares priced at Rs 615-648. The company reported a Q1 FY25 loss of Rs 14.14 crore, despite a 19 per cent revenue growth to Rs 535.31 crore. This entirely Offer For Sale (OFS) issue will see funds go to existing shareholders.

news.title: DLF Cyber City Developers raises ₹1,100 crore through NCDs
news.para: DLF's rental arm, DCCDL, successfully raised Rs 1,100 crore through a private placement of non-convertible debentures at a 6.91% coupon rate. This funding comes as the joint venture, which holds 44 million sq ft of commercial spaces, reported a 26% increase in net profit to Rs 593 crore in the June quarter.

news.title: Pankaj Tripathi and family buy two apartments for ₹10.85 crore in Mumbai
news.para: Pankaj Tripathi, his wife Mridula, and daughter Aashi acquired two apartments in Mumbai for a cumulative value of ₹10.85 crore. The primary residence, costing ₹9.98 crore, is located in Andheri West, while a second apartment worth ₹87 lakh was purchased in Kandivali West. These property transactions were registered in July and September 2025.

news.title: S2W Media Deepens Global Footprint with Strategic Move to Pune’s AP4 Tech Park
news.para: The global B2B demand-generation leader reinforces its India commitment with a 50,000 sq. ft. space at Amar Builders & Pristine Properties' flagship development.

news.title: Property tax rebate window closes today, Ludhiana mayor plea to avoid 20% hit
news.para: Ludhiana offers a 10% property tax rebate for payments made by September 30 for FY 2025-26. City leaders stressed timely payments are crucial for development. Penalties for late payments begin October 1, escalating to 20% plus 18% annual interest after March 31.

news.title: Ghaziabad civic body allows property tax rebate for one more month
news.para: Ghaziabad Municipal Corporation has extended its property tax rebate deadline to October 31, offering a 20% discount to maximise revenue. Subsequent rebates will be 10% in November 2025 and 5% for December and January 2026, before fines apply. With over 5.50 lakh taxpayers, GMC aims to collect 80% of the state's Rs 600 crore target for FY 2025-26.

news.title: PM Svamitva Yojana brings legal ownership & financial empowerment to rural Andhra Pradesh
news.para: Rural Andhra Pradesh families lacked land ownership documents for generations. The PM Svamitva Yojana now addresses this issue. Advanced technology like drones maps village properties precisely. This scheme provides legal ownership certificates to villagers. It resolves disputes and enables financial independence. The initiative also identifies government lands and boosts local panchayat revenue.
